<p>This command form will allow you to issue Majordomo administrative
commands by name.  Some commands, like <b>report-summary</b>, 
have a hyphen in their names.  The part that follows the hyphen 
is called the <i>command mode</i>.
</p>
<p>
There are several steps required to use the command form.
</p>
<ol>
  <li>Choose a command from the <b>Command</b> menu.</li>

  <li>Make sure the mailing list in the <b>Mailing List</b> box
  is correct.</li>

  <li>An administrative password is required to use this form.
  The password for your mailing list should already be marked by 
  14 asterisks in the <b>Password</b> box.  If this is not true, 
  type an administrative password into the box.</li>

  <li>If additional information is needed to issue
  a command, type that information into the box
  immediately to the right of the command menu.</li>

  <li>Press the <b>Issue Command</b> button.</li>
</ol>

<p>
To learn more about a particular command, select <b>help</b> in the 
command menu, type the name of the command (without the command mode) 
into the box immediately to the right, and press the <b>Issue Command</b> 
button.  You will see a summary of how the command works.
</p>
